article.headline: Fla Atlantic 91, Mercer 80
article.story: BOCA RATON, Fla. (AP) -- DeAndre Rice scored a team-high of 20 points and five assists to help Florida Atlantic defeat Mercer 91 to 80 Saturday. During his first game for Florida Atlantic, Carlos Monroe scored 14 points and four rebounds in 18 minutes. In the first half Florida Atlantic (5-7) took the lead with 42-38. With 5:13 left the Owls' had a 17-point advantage, 72-55, their largest of the season, and the 11-point margin of victory was their first in double figures this year. Mercer (3-8) was led by Andrew Brown and Jacob Skogen with 24 points each. Rodney Webb added 16 points and four steals and Fred Marshall scored 15 points for Florida Atlantic.
